---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy — Online Image Convertor (We Don't See Your Images)"
  description="Privacy summary for our Online Image Convertor. Your image files never leave your browser — plain-language summary of what we do and don't collect."
  keywords="online image convertor privacy, image converter privacy, private image converter, no upload converter privacy"
  robots="index, follow"
>
  <section class="page-container privacy-page">
    <header class="privacy-header">
      <span class="t-caption-mono eyebrow">Privacy</span>
      <h1 class="t-display-xl">Privacy summary.</h1>
      <p class="t-body-lg sub">
        The short version: your image data stays on your device.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="tl-dr card-lg elev-2">
      <h2 class="t-display-sm">TL;DR</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Your image files never leave your browser.</strong> Conversion happens locally using the Canvas API.</li>
        <li><strong>We don't have accounts.</strong> So we can't link any activity to a person.</li>
        <li><strong>We use Google Analytics</strong> for aggregate page-view statistics (anonymized IP). It does not see your image data.</li>
        <li><strong>No first-party cookies.</strong> Aside from Google Analytics' own cookies, we set none.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="privacy-body">
      <h2 class="t-display-md">What we collect</h2>
      <p class="t-body-md">
        We use Google Analytics 4 with IP anonymization enabled. This gives us aggregate, anonymous statistics about page views, browser/OS distribution, and which converter pages get used. We do not collect, transmit, or store the contents of any image you process. Image processing happens entirely in your browser via JavaScript.
      </p>

      <h2 class="t-display-md">What Google Analytics sees</h2>
      <p class="t-body-md">
        GA receives the standard browser metadata: page URL, anonymized IP, browser user-agent, referrer. It does <em>not</em> receive file names, file sizes, or anything about the image data you convert.
      </p>

      <h2 class="t-display-md">Opting out</h2>
      <p class="t-body-md">
        Standard browser-level Do Not Track or any privacy extension that blocks <code>googletagmanager.com</code> will fully exclude you from analytics with no impact on the converter's functionality.
      </p>

      <h2 class="t-display-md">Contact</h2>
      <p class="t-body-md">
        Questions about this page? <a href="mailto:hi@realonlineruler.com">hi@realonlineruler.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .privacy-page {
    padding-block: 64px 32px;
    max-width: 800px;
  }
  .privacy-header {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .privacy-page { padding-block: 40px 24px; }
    .tl-dr { margin-bottom: 24px; }
    .privacy-body h2 { margin-top: 8px; }
  }
  .eyebrow { color: var(--color-mute); }
  .sub { color: var(--color-body); max-width: 580px; margin: 0; }

  .tl-dr {
    background-color: var(--color-canvas-soft);
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }
  .tl-dr h2 { margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .tl-dr ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .tl-dr li {
    color: var(--color-body);
    padding-left: 28px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .tl-dr li::before {
    content: "✓";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    width: 18px;
    height: 18px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background-color: rgba(10, 138, 62, 0.12);
    color: #0a8a3e;
    font-size: 11px;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .tl-dr strong { color: var(--color-ink); }

  .privacy-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }
  .privacy-body h2 { margin: 16px 0 4px; }
  .privacy-body p { color: var(--color-body); margin: 0; max-width: 720px; }
  .privacy-body a { color: var(--color-link); }
  .privacy-body code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    background-color: var(--color-canvas-soft);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
</style>
